1 AMEND House Substitute for House Bill No. 2576, Page 1, Section A, Line 5, by inserting after
2 said section and line the following:
3
4 "9.025. The month of January is hereby designated as "Blood Donor Awareness Month".
5 It is recommended to the people of this state that the month be appropriately observed through
6 activities that increase awareness of the importance of blood donation. The state deems blood
7 and blood products to be a critical resource and a vital public health asset that must be readily
8 available at all times."; and
9
10 Further amend said bill by amending the title, enacting clause, and intersectional references
11 accordingly.
